# ── COMMIT-MSG HOOK ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Runs AFTER you write a commit message but BEFORE the commit is finalised.
# Validates that the message follows conventional commit format:
#   type(scope): description
#   e.g. feat(auth): add login endpoint
#        fix(ci): correct eslint config
#
# Valid types: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, perf, test, build, ci, chore, revert
# If the message doesn't match, the commit is rejected.

npx --no -- commitlint --edit "$1"
